{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Structure","symbolKind":"struct","externalID":"s:4GLib7DateRefV","title":"DateRef","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DateRef","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"DateRef","kind":"identifier"}]},"abstract":[{"code":"GDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a struct for calendrical calculations.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/dateref"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(_:)-15l2w","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(_:)-5vh9g","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(_:)-6v7fp","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(_:)-7pk3a","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(_:)-9375e","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(dmy:month:year:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(julian:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"]},{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/ptr"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/new(dmy:month:year:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/new(julian:)"],"title":"Type Methods","anchor":"Type-Methods"},{"title":"Default Implementations","generated":true,"anchor":"Default-Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/DateProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef\/PointerWrapper-Implementations"]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateProtocol","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DateRef","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"text":" data structure represents a day between January 1, Year 1,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and sometime a few thousand years in the future (right now it will go"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to the year 65535 or so, but [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.set_parse"},{"type":"text","text":"] only parses up to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"year 8000 or so - just count on “a few thousand”). "},{"code":"GDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is meant to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"represent everyday dates, not astronomical dates or historical dates","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"or ISO timestamps or the like. It extrapolates the current Gregorian"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"calendar forward and backward in time; there is no attempt to change","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the calendar to match time periods or locations. "},{"code":"GDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" does not store"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time information; it represents a day."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" implementation has several nice features; it is only a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"64-bit struct, so storing large numbers of dates is very efficient. It","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"can keep both a Julian and day-month-year representation of the date,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"since some calculations are much easier with one representation or the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"other. A Julian representation is simply a count of days since some"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fixed day in the past; for ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date","type":"reference"},{"text":" the fixed day is January 1, 1 AD.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(“Julian” dates in the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" API aren’t really Julian dates in the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"technical sense; technically, Julian dates count from the start of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Julian period, Jan 1, 4713 BC).","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"GDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is simple to use. First you need a “blank” date; you can get a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"dynamically allocated date from [ctor"},{"code":"GLib.Date.new","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"], or you can declare an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"automatic variable or array and initialize it by calling [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.clear"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"A cleared date is safe; it’s safe to call [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.set_dmy"},{"type":"text","text":"] and the other"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"mutator functions to initialize the value of a cleared date. However, a cleared date"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is initially invalid, meaning that it doesn’t represent a day that exists."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It is undefined to call any of the date calculation routines on an invalid date.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If you obtain a date from a user or other unpredictable source, you should check","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"its validity with the [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.valid"},{"type":"text","text":"] predicate. [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.valid"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is also used to check for errors with [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.set_parse"},{"text":"] and other functions","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that can fail. Dates can be invalidated by calling [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Date.clear"},{"text":"] again.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is very important to use the API to access the "},{"code":"GDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct. Often only the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"day-month-year or only the Julian representation is valid. Sometimes neither is valid."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Use the API."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GLib also features "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDateTime"},{"type":"text","text":" which represents a precise time."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef"},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"code":"GDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Date"},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateRef","type":"reference"},{"text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDate"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note"}]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateRef/init(opaquePointer:)":{"title":"init(opaquePointer:)","type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/dateref\/init(opaquepointer:)","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"opaquePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s13OpaquePointerV","text":"OpaquePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Unsafe 